create_ps_per_micron_model(25.10)            create_ps_per_micron_model(25.10)

Name
       create_ps_per_micron_model - Derives psPM.model as a separate command

Syntax
       create_ps_per_micron_model

       [-help]

       [-overwrite]

       Derives  psPM.model as a separate command. This command is used for ac-
       tive logic flat top model generation.  For  non-ART  model  generation,
       psPM.model  can  still  be generated during create_proto_model step. It
       supports MMMC where it can automatically generate a psPM model file for
       each delay corner. with this, you can do corner dependent psPM  budget-
       ing  and generated hold budgeting that is accurate where correct corner
       is used for hold instead of using one corner for both hold and setup.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for each create_ps_per_micron_model parameter.  For a
              detailed description of the command and all its parameters,  use
              the man command: man create_ps_per_micron_model.

       -overwrite
              Overwrites an existing psPM.model.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Examples
       The  following  commands  generate  psPM.model  before running the cre-
       ate_proto_model command:

       restoreDesign DBS/init_design.enc.dat dtmf_recvr_core

       create_ps_per_micron_model

       identify_proto_model

       create_proto_model -flat_top DBS/model_gen.enc

